Beerio Statistics

Updated: Mar 11, 2020

This document tracks Beerio game statistics. The last tracked games were 6 games played on Tuesday, March 10, 2020 by Neil, Shawn, Chuck, and Steve.

All Game Data

This table contains scores and events for all logged games. It is searchable and sortable on all columns.

Descriptive Statistics

This table depicts overall Beerio statistics for all tracked players. Recent Average is calculated as the average score from the last date the player played.

Figures

The first figure depicts Beerio scores over games in each day. Punishments are indicated by a blue shell. Days with only one game are excluded.

The next plot pools the data across evenings to show the change in average score for each player as the evening wears on. Points indicate scores for each match, jittered horizontally to reduce overplotting. Lines are simple linear regressions of score on game number. Note the trend is relatively similar across players. Each additional game is associated with a score difference of -0.88 (95% CI: -1.45, -0.3).

The next plot depicts overall score distributions for each player as a violina symmetrical density plot. Wider cross-sections indicate more games with scores in that range. Points indicate scores for each match, jittered horizontally to reduce overplotting. The line inside the violin denotes the median score.

The last plot depicts the overall score distribution with mean (26.4) and median (28). Green bar sections indicate scores receiving shots.

Round Data

This section depicts the round-level data which contains information on scores in specific maps. Due to difficulty, it may be recorded less frequently than game-level data. The table below shows all recorded rounds.

The next table displays average scores for each player on each course.

The first plot show average scores for each player on each map. Courses are sorted by their overall mean scorethe map with the current highest mean score is Lunar Colony.

The next plot shows differences between each players overall average score and their average for the given course. For example, the plot indicates the difference between Neils overall average and his Sweet Sweet Kingdom average is -2.9.

The last plot provides an alternate visualization of the same information.
